"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-adam-burgess-canoe-slalom-silver-team-gb-b1173585.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Adam Burgessclaimed his first Olympic medal with canoe slalom singles silver at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium in Paris.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1056125471613696e-16, \"text\": \"Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\"}, {\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.523523524413881e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Stoke-on-Trent paddler, the fourth-fastest finisher from the semi-finals, put in a superb run save a small error on upstream gate 17, but recovered at the bottom of the course, crossing the finish in 96.84 seconds for the fastest run of the final with three men left to challenge.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgess was still sitting in gold medal position when home favourite Nicolas Gestin, the reigning world silver medallist, left his best run for last, destroying the Briton's leading time in 91.36, 5.48 seconds faster than the British runner-up, with Slovakia's Matej Benus rounding out the podium.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Gestin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\"}, {\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.6249827336209203, \"rank\": 0.5304266382305213, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8732002902147363, \"rank\": 0.13775036369038118, \"text\": \"Slovakia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was redemption for Burgess, who avenged his maiden final from three summers ago in Tokyo, where the now-32-year-old finished fourth and missed out on a medal by just 0.16 seconds.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.997375651685519, \"rank\": 0.00263124630393705, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was another magical moment for the British paddlers after Kimberley Woods collected bronze in the women's kayak singles on Sunday, and just as she vowed she would do after her own magical moment - was in the stands cheering on her team-mate.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1181, \"end\": 1188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.6249827336209203, \"rank\": 0.5304266382305213, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kimberley Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgess' jaw dropped when he realised he was guaranteed a medal after Germany's Sideris Tasiadis, who pipped him to Bronze in Tokyo, did not do enough for a podium place in Paris with his 97.27 - and it just became a matter of which colour he would collect.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1459, \"end\": 1466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9990424408550627, \"rank\": 0.0008972548106770223, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sideris_Tasiadis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sideris Tasiadis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sideris_Tasiadis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sideris_Tasiadis\"}, {\"begin\": 1515, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.997375651685519, \"rank\": 0.00263124630393705, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1562, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.523523524413881e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter  And it was gold for the hosts, the already-boisterous home crowd - despite the blazing heat - roaring as their man crossed the line for his blistering championship finish.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgess finished fourth-fastest from the afternoon's semis in 97.21 seconds, a penalty-free run that nevertheless highlighted a few areas of improvement as he navigated a tricky middle section, keeping calm to assure himself a chance at a medal.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Stoke City supporter became Great Britain's first ever canoe slalom Under-23 world champion in 2015, and claimed C1 individual silver at the European Championships in Prague before taking home bronze in the team event at the World Championships in Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2327, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stoke_City_F.C.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2909374170615107e-15, \"text\": \"Stoke City\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stoke_City_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stoke_City_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 2355, \"end\": 2368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999866861808, \"rank\": 1.3254015934865627e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9999999512488115, \"rank\": 4.875099984436798e-08, \"text\": \"C1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 2494, \"end\": 2500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AC_Sparta_Prague\", \"score\": 0.5771579104334809, \"rank\": 0.7326280761629136, \"text\": \"Prague\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AC_Sparta_Prague\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AC_Sparta_Prague\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.979666818227308e-15, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is a five-time world medallist, all in team events, including silver at last September's home championships at Lee Valley.\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2706, \"end\": 2716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Valley_White_Water_Centre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2534627974263993e-19, \"text\": \"Lee Valley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Valley_White_Water_Centre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Valley_White_Water_Centre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 3597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2779, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.999994409419453, \"rank\": 5.3884721975195565e-06, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.999994409419453, \"rank\": 5.3884721975195565e-06, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_I